Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta electrode layers with three different microstructures were manufactured by screen-printing, spin-coating and infiltration into a porous Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 backbone.
Titulo: Effect of Microstructure on the Degradation of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ Electrodes in Dry and Humid Atmospheres

Sentencas: Electrode performance was monitored at 700 degrees C in 20% O-2 over periods of 1,600 to 3,860 h by means of electrochemical impedance spectroscopy under open circuit conditions.
Titulo: Effect of Microstructure on the Degradation of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ Electrodes in Dry and Humid Atmospheres

Sentencas: Reference measurements were performed in dry atmospheres, where significant electrode activation was observed for cells with spin-coated and infiltrated electrodes.
Titulo: Effect of Microstructure on the Degradation of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ Electrodes in Dry and Humid Atmospheres

Sentencas: Subsequently, the relative humidity level in the surrounding atmosphere was set to 30% and further raised to 60%, thus simulating SOFC operation with ambient air without pre-drying.
Titulo: Effect of Microstructure on the Degradation of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ Electrodes in Dry and Humid Atmospheres

Sentencas: While no performance loss could be observed in dry atmospheres, significant degradation occurred in humid atmospheres with pronounced differences between degradation rates of half cells with different electrode microstructures.
Titulo: Effect of Microstructure on the Degradation of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ Electrodes in Dry and Humid Atmospheres

Sentencas: Post-test analyses by scanning electron microscopy (SEM) and transmissionscanning electron microscopy (STEM) were employed to identify the causes for the observed differences in degradation behavior.
Titulo: Effect of Microstructure on the Degradation of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ Electrodes in Dry and Humid Atmospheres

Sentencas: For screen-printed cells, the surface of the degraded electrodes was covered with small crystallites, probably consisting of SrO formed by Sr-segregation and surface precipitation, where humidity was found to be a crucial factor.
Titulo: Effect of Microstructure on the Degradation of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ Electrodes in Dry and Humid Atmospheres

Sentencas: For spin-coated and infiltrated electrodes, poisoning by impurities (Si, Cr, S) and particle coarsening were identified as potential causes.
Titulo: Effect of Microstructure on the Degradation of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ Electrodes in Dry and Humid Atmospheres
